    <div class="content-section">
        <p><span class="highlight">Program Name:</span> Disaster Response, Rescue Operations, and Vulnerability Analysis</p>
        <p><span class="highlight">Venue:</span> Guptkasi, Uttarakhand</p>
        <p><span class="highlight">Date:</span> 25-12-2024</p>

        <h2>Program Overview</h2>
        <p>The Mountain Forum Himalayas organized a one-day training program on December 25, 2024, in Gupt Kashi, Rudra Prayag District, Uttarakhand. This program, attended by 34 participants from 10 villages, focused on equipping attendees with knowledge and skills to respond to disasters effectively and analyze vulnerabilities in their communities.</p>

        <h2>Key Highlights</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="highlight">Disaster Awareness:</span> Participants learned about the causes and types of disasters, as well as the provisions of the Disaster Management Act of 2005.</li>
            <li><span class="highlight">Risk Reduction Techniques:</span> Strategies to minimize disaster risks, including utilizing local resources, were demonstrated.</li>
            <li><span class="highlight">Practical Skills:</span> Techniques for casualty handling, such as the fireman's lift, improvised stretchers, and CPR, were taught and practiced.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Expert Contributions</h2>
        <p>Hira Lal Thakur, a Disaster Risk Reduction expert, provided insights into disaster management, vulnerability analysis, and effective community-level risk reduction strategies. Experts Beli Ram Negi and Suresh Kumar demonstrated practical rescue techniques, including casualty carrying methods and CPR. Participants practiced these techniques and were encouraged to share them within their communities.</p>

        <div class="image-section">
            <img src="/disaster-training.jpg" alt="Disaster Response Training at Gupt Kashi">
        </div>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>The training session was well-received by the participants, who expressed their gratitude for the valuable knowledge and practical skills imparted. The program fostered awareness and preparedness, equipping communities with the tools to reduce disaster risks effectively.</p>
